1 3. The cardiac emergency response plan template must integrate core elements
2 established by the American heart association or other nationally recognized
3 organization. The plan must require:
4 a. Establishment of a school cardiac emergency response team.
5 b. Activation of the team when an individual experiences sudden cardiac arrest.
6 c. Placement of automated external defibrillators on school grounds.
7 d. Routine maintenance of automated external defibrillators.
8 e. Distribution of the plan on school grounds.
9 f. Stipulation of appropriate school personnel, including licensed coaches, school
10 nurses, and athletic trainers, to receive training.
11 g. Periodic training of stipulated school personnel to perform cardiopulmonary
12 resuscitation, use an automated external defibrillator, and administer firs t - aid .
13 h. Annual practice by faculty and students of the plan using drills.
14 i. Coordination with local emergency medical services providers.
15 j. Annual review and evaluation of the plan.
16 4. Each public and nonpublic school shall:
17 a. Using the template provided by the superintendent of public instruction, develop
18 a cardiac emergency response plan for use by school personnel when an
19 individual experiences sudden cardiac arrest or a similar life-threatening
20 emergency on school grounds, including an athletic venue, or at a school-
21 sponsored athletic event.
22 b. Place each automated external defibrillator on school grounds according to the
23 guidelines established by the American heart association or an organization
24 focused on emergency cardiovascular care.
25 c. Place an automated external defibrillator in an easily accessible location at each
26 school athletic venue and event.
27 d. Identify each automated external defibrillator with appropriate signage.
28 e. Make each automated external defibrillator available in an unlocked location that
29 allows the automated external defibrillator to be retrieved and placed on an
30 individual experiencing cardiac arrest in fewer than three minutes.
