1 SECTION 2. AMENDMENT. Subsection 1 of section 15.1-06-06 of the North Dakota
2 Century Code is amended and reenacted as follows:
3 1. To obtain certification that a public school is approved, the superintendent of the
4 district in which the school is located shall submit to the superintendent of public
5 instruction a compliance report verifying that:
6 a. Each classroom teacher is licensed to teach by the education standards and
7 practices board or approved to teach by the education standards and practices
8 board;
9 b. Each classroom teacher is teaching only in those course areas or fields for which
10 the teacher is licensed or for which the teacher has received an exception under
11 section 15.1-09-57;
12 c. The school meets all curricular requirements set forth in chapter 15.1-21;
13 d. The school participates in and meets the requirements of a review process that
14 is:
15 (1) Designed to improve student achievement through a continuous cycle of
16 improvement; and
17 (2) Approved by the superintendent of public instruction;
18 e. The physical school plant has been inspected by the state fire marshal or the
19 state fire marshal's designee in accordance with section 15.1-06-09 and:
20 (1) Has no unremedied deficiency; or
21 (2) Has deficiencies that have been addressed in a plan of correction which
22 was submitted to and approved by the state fire marshal or the state fire
23 marshal's designee;
24 f. All individuals hired after June 30, 2011, and having unsupervised contact with
25 students at the school, have:
26 (1) Undergone a criminal history background check requested by the employing
27 school district; or
28 (2) Undergone a criminal history background check in order to be licensed by
29 the education standards and practices board or by any other state licensing
30 board; and
